  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0ba8\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc2\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b95\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0b9a\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bbf \u0b86\u0bb2\u0baf \u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4 \u0bae\u0bb9\u0bcb\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb5\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb4\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bcb\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd -  \u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb4\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba8\u0b95\u0bb0 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Nallur Kandaswamy Temple Annual Festival will be held as usual - Jaffna Mayor",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "A discussion on the arrangements for the annual festival of the historic Nallur Kandaswamy Temple was held at the Jaffna Municipal Council Health Medical Officer's Office on Wednesday 29th.",
        "Jaffna Mayor Manivannan said that the Nallur festival, which has been limited to the last three years due to the Easter blast and corona infection, will be held as usual, this time as it was before 2018.",
        "Traffic around the Nallur temple will be closed from the morning of August 1 and will reopen only after the completion of Vairavar Shanti on August 29.",
        "Vehicles for any reason other than the Municipal Water Supply Cart and Sewage Cart will not be allowed to enter the restricted areas along the red and white flags by the temple administration around the Temple Outside Street. Similarly, no business activities can be carried out within the roadblocks bordered by white flags. Video cannot be recorded using drone cameras.",
        "All the gallows that come to the temple to pay the dues can only be entered through the front Point Street of the temple. Arrangements have been made for all vehicles to exit Chetty Street once the oncoming cavalry is unloaded.",
        "Vehicles coming through Point Pedro Road during road closures can reach Jaffna by traveling on the road in front of the Jaffna Municipal Council. But the concert can be traveled along Nallur Road during the night and sabbatical festivals.",
        "Health restrictions will not be observed during the festival this time. Yet every individual must take care and act on their health",
        "Apart from these, we will issue notices regarding the restrictions in the near future as and when required.",
        "Many concerned departmental officials including the Deputy Chief Minister, representatives of the Nallur Temple Administrator, members of the Municipal Council, municipal officials and public health inspectors were present."
      ],
